- Community post card.

16. Error Handling
- Show user-friendly messages.
- Retry failed requests.
- Preserve unsent drafts locally.
- Handle slow internet gracefully.
- Handle expired sessions cleanly.
- Provide empty-state and loading-state UI for every major screen.

17. Authentication Flow
- User logs in or signs up.
- Token is stored securely.
- App loads profile and exam settings.
- Session refresh happens silently.
- If auth fails, user is redirected to login.

18. API Integration
The Flutter app should consume the backend through repositories and service classes.
- Use typed models.
- Centralize endpoint paths.
- Separate request and response mapping.
- Add interceptors for auth and logging.

